Hello to all. it been a long time since I have posted anything, mostly do to the fact that I have been thinking alot...maybe to much. I guess I start with my weekend thus far

Friday night I want to sears to get some empty box to put stuff in for when we move, but instead of going home after I got the boxes I decide that I was going to hang out in the mall. I thought I was going to be all alone because Scott refuses to go to the mall anymore and Joan works. So I walked walk from sears, stopping at The Picture People store, across from boarders and next to old navy, to see if my friend Stacy was working but sadly I did not find her there. Then I walk across to boarders to see if Jay Jay was working but again I found no one.

So believing I would not find anyone in the mall I knew/liked I just walk aimlessly though the masses of people the came to start X-MAS shopping to beat the rush, the only thing is everyone has the same damn idea and the shopping flooded the mall. Anyway I was walking to the other side of the mall and out of the no where I was Bruce walking towards me. It was a quick hello but it was nice to know I know someone at the mall. 

About 15 seconds later I saw Christie, which totally turn my day around. She gave me a b-day gift which was super nice of her to do. Its been a long time since I got a gift from anyone and its great to know that someones thinking of you. (By the way I can't remember if I said thank you to you Christie so thank you, I love the cd ^_^) 

So now I was no longer alone, we walk towards the food court talking about this and that, sometimes not saying anything, but it was still nice. I don't know how to explain the rested of the night. All I can say it was a nice night. Everything just seem right...mostly. I not sure how many times this happen over the course of 4 hours, but I think she hit her head about 11 times ^_^. At least 5 were my fault but still 11 times it still alot. Come on Christie ^_^. 

Also I saw Jay Jay, Muff, and Mary Ann at the mall at around 8:15 ish. yea i haven't seen muff in a while, he seems to been in good spirits. Well my dear friends I am off for tonight.

hi everyone. i know its been a long time since i have posted but i have to find out something. so if anyone know a girl named anna that goes to north please let me know

any way i dug a hole in the ground, put him in a box and the rest is history.

the past couple of days and never said hi. Its not the i didn'tf see you,

i am back for that hellish place known to the world New Hampshire (is that the right spelling. i am having a hard time understanding it but i do wish to start school again. i must be suck or something but that is how i feel...sad isn't it. well summer is at its end. so back to sopping was a must.  so about a week ago i want shopping instead of working, but i still punch in. that that sears hahahahaha. as i walked away from sears i looked in boarders and who do you think i saw. the sexyest man with a fro Bruce and of course Kendra. rock'n no?. anyway a walk around with them for abouts an hour and half. and then i found scott who also left work early. so then  i play ddr with him for a bit. but scott had to go home so then i start to shop. i bought the coolest red and black shoes, a kill bill shirt just coz it sexy, another pair of shants. and a couple of dress shirts. and some other junk. oh yea i got ghost in the shell:stand alone complex and it is very goddly. 

this passed saturday i went to the mall with jon and we ddr for about 5 hours or so. very fun.jon said i got better i don't think so. anyway jon wants to make a band so we talk about and it seems we have all the intraments (i can't spell) we need to make a band. the only problem is we have no one to play them :P. i think we need some to play the keyboard which i can provide. jon going to try his hand at singing. i can't wait to see if he is as good as i hope he is. he a great writer so the question is can he sing that songs. well their is only one way to find out and thats by playing.

well tonight was grand. i got to play ddr until some short little fat kid broke the right pad's down arrow, i hate fat kids that have no idea how to play. all you have to do is step on the arrow not put your fat little foot through it...any we (me, scott, joan, carlos, mike m, and mike g) saw Hero. it is truly godly. i have work tomarrow afternoon, sadness, but i think my friend Christie is coming to save me for sears. any way boys and girl i am out for the night...maybe

well, life is great, no really i am super happy. Tomorrow i get to work in the electronic department at sears (yea i am no longer in shoes), and since tomorrow there is no tax in mass. i going to make a ton of money off comission by selling tv's and stuff...or i would of if i got off the stupid traning pay X.x. So i just going to work all day and make no money how fun.

i went to the mall with scott and bruce, and of course jon was there. so we ddr...ed for about 4 1/2 hours. funness. mmm... what else...oh yea i lefted all my money at my house so i was going to use an atm. jon was going to go to target to buy food and said i should use the atm near there.  so me and jon walked down to target and jon bought about 10-12 dollers worth of snack bar and oddly enough 4 pair of boxers. the odd part is we never picked up a cart or the hand cart thingies so we walked around target with 5 boxes of snack bar and underwear. oh yea went jon was looking for a pair a boxer he throught a pair and it hit someone. :) it was truly funny. after we lefted target i walked over to the atm and found out it was broken. 

the moral of my rant is i have no luck with money. 

ps. lasgo is godly

i have have been noticing (over the past few year) that something my hands twich uncontrolablilly for a few minutes. my mom believe i have a nevre problem. i am not sure that it. i me wouldn't i noticed something sooner or somethings. anyway i have some kind of cat scan thing eventuly. oh well. i don't think i have much to worry about...long live the steve.

well today i went to the mall and played ddr for about 4 hour. it would have been great but i was alone for the four hours. sucks. oh well. it gave me time to think about a few things

1) i realized that i have wasted 2/3 of the summer. What have i done. nothing but work. and what do i have to show for it. nothing. 

2) i miss school. i know, steve your an idiot, but i miss it. i don't know why.

I final found time to write. of course it is now 2:10. i have been working all week and now i have realized i have no life. its sad really. i sleep and work. that about it. I have 37 hour next week in sears. it sucks. and the pay is shitty. i cut my hand open with a box cutter, hopefully it will get fucked up and i can sue. well i got to sleep now because i have work tomm... today. damn shoes, sears and lands end. Well at least i am only working until 5pm today. 

good world see you again in 3 hours.

I am tired of sears. i got more hours there, which i was hoping for because of summer, but i did not wish for 35 hour a week i am working everyday these week. and there not short shifts anymore, oh no there 8.5 hours long. damn sears i feel it killing slowly. it is as if i was being poked with a pin, and each poke only take one drop of my life away.
